<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920313-0147</DOCNO><DOCID>920313-0147.</DOCID><HL>   Sterling Optical's Request</HL><DATE>03/13/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   EYE</CO><MS>CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)MEDICAL SUPPLIES (MDS)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>BANKRUPTCY (BCY)STOCK MARKET NEWS (STK)ACQUISITIONS, MERGERS, TAKEOVERS (TNM)</NS><RE>NEW JERSEY (NJ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   HACKENSACK, N.J. -- Sterling Optical Corp., an eyewearretailer operating under bankruptcy law protection, asked theNew York Stock Exchange to permanently cease trading thecompany's shares.   The company made the request after creditors decided notto attempt to reorganize the company. Sterling is sellingsubstantially all of its assets to the owners of CohenFashion Optical, Hewlett, N.Y., for $15 million.</LP><TEXT>   The company said there will be no value to currentshareholders after payment to creditors. The New York StockExchange halted trading in Sterling shares yesterday, pendingan announcement from the company. The last quote for Sterlingshares was 37.5 cents a share.</TEXT></DOC>